news.title: Two key Signa divisions filing for insolvency in hit to real-estate empire
news.para: GERMANY-PROPERTY/SIGNA (UPDATE 3, PIX)UPDATE 3-Two key Signa divisions filing for insolvency in hit to real-estate empire

news.title: Indian real estate: The transformative journey in 2024 and ahead
news.para: The year 2023 gave a fillip to the upward mobility in India’s residential housing market. The Reserve Bank of India’s move to keep interest rates steady empowered homebuyers to invest in their dream homes, enabling a wider population to become homeowners.

news.title: Dubai’s red-hot property market is bracing for a slowdown
news.para: So far, the boom has been underpinned by an influx of wealthy investors such as Russians seeking to shield their assets, crypto millionaires and rich Indians seeking second homes.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to disburse first instalment to beneficiaries
news.para: Affordable housing through credit linked subsidy under PMAY(Urban) is allowed for beneficiaries from EWS with an annual household income up to Rs 3,00,000 and house sizes upto 30sq.m.

news.title: Noida: NMRC clears Aqua Line extension plan, to be ready in 36 months after government nod
news.para: ​On Wednesday, Noida Metro gave a go-ahead to the 11.6km corridor that will have eight stations — most of them in residential sectors along the Noida expressway that has emerged as a housing hub.

news.title: Dehradun: Doon Valley draft notification out for public suggestions
news.para: The proposed changes include the preparation of plans such as tourism, grazing, master plan of development, and others by the state government with input from relevant departments.

news.title: Land use of facilities may not be fixed under Indore master plan 2041
news.para: It was proposed in the master plan that land use of different facilities including residential, commercial and industrial, will not be fixed. But permissions will be given based on width of the roads.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to auction off eight plots in January 2024
news.para: After an unsuccessful attempt to auction plots in February this year, the civic body had on November 29 decided to auction eight new plots once again.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body seals Mantri Square mall over tax issue
news.para: BBMP officials said the mall has property tax dues of over Rs 51 crore.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC decides not to hike property tax
news.para: "We approach the next financial year towards making NDMC an aspirational city and global benchmark befitting its status as the national capital of ‘Viksit Bharat’,” said council chairman Amit Yadav.

news.title: IBBI prepares list of 787 insolvency professionals to expedite resolution process
news.para: The move is aimed at avoiding administrative delays in the appointment of IPs to expedite insolvency resolution and prevent further erosion of stressed asset value, said a senior official.

news.title: Don't compel Jewar farmers to sell land: Allahabad HC to Noida administration
news.para: The court, however, made it clear that the state authorities could acquire the land by following procedures prescribed by the law.

news.title: Chandigarh: F&CC gives nod to 17 more construction & demolition collection points
news.para: During the monthly meeting, the committee discussed and approved multiple agenda items. The meeting was held under the supervision of mayor Anup Gupta and was attended by elected members and senior administrative and engineering officers of the civic body.

news.title: HUDCO inks pact with Gujarat to invest Rs 14,500 crore to finance housing, urban infra projects
news.para: ​The state government intends for overall development of Gujarat by implementing various housing and infrastructure projects, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Pune: Auction of 50 commercial properties finalized for January 2024
news.para: Before auction, the civic body explores different options to recover property tax like issuance of notices, attaching the property and sealing it for a temporary period.

news.title: Industrial plots to cost 12% more in Greater Noida
news.para: So, plots measuring up to 1,000sqm (quarter of an acre) will be available at the rate of Rs 29,238 per sqm. Similarly, land parcels from 1,001-20,000sqm will cost upwards of Rs 23,975. There has been no change in the price of plots bigger than 20,000sqm.

news.title: Panchkula: Self-certify property to get 15% tax rebate
news.para: MC commissioner Sachin Gupta said the urban local bodies (ULB) have decided to give rebate on property tax in the current financial year 2023-2024.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 25,000 properties under tax net in six months; adds Rs 46 crore in revenue
news.para: Out of these 25,000, 60% of the properties are from the two divisions alone: Panchavati and Cidco. NMC officials said that the civic body will get additional Rs 46 crore revenue through these properties.
